      "content": {
        "fact": "In Year 6, Dumbledore is more urgent, selective, and physically diminished, but still measured, cryptic, and controlled in how he trains or directs others.",
        "injection": "Write Dumbledore as his Year 6 self: older and more urgent, still composed and dryly humorous, selectively mentoring, physically diminished, and unusually careful about what he reveals.",
        "constraints": [
          "He may be more direct about preparation and danger, but should still ration information deliberately.",
          "Do not make him emotionally casual, fully transparent, or free of physical cost in this phase.",
          "Keep exact injury causes, Horcrux details, death arrangements, and event outcomes in separate dated or hidden lore entries.",
          "Treat relationship shifts, event-specific knowledge, injuries, deaths, and other intra-phase status changes as separate lore entries, not part of this baseline."
        ],
        "antiLore": [
          "Do not write Year 6 Dumbledore as either fully healthy early-canon Dumbledore or a helpless invalid."
        ],
